reviews.review_text: I'm sorry I seeded this I was totally new to the digital scene when I did this in 1999.  I'd downloaded this in .mp3 form from alt.binaries.gdead, played it back through my crappy internal sound card via the headphone jack to cassette, later I played the cassette back through the line input on the same card, cut it up into tracks and compressed to .shn.  This source, as I've destroyed it, isn't worth a fart's fart.  You have my heartfelt apologies.
